    "body": "while cycle over subscripted type is less optimised than unsubscripted one - see comparison below:\n\nsimple dictionary:\n```c\n/* \"b.pyx\":17\n *·\n * cdef myfunc(d: dict):\n *     while d:             # <<<<<<<<<<<<<<\n *         print('a')\n*/\n  while (1) {\n    {\n      Py_ssize_t __pyx_temp = __Pyx_PyDict_GET_SIZE(__pyx_v_d);\n      if (unlikely(((!CYTHON_ASSUME_SAFE_SIZE) && __pyx_temp < 0))) __PYX_ERR(0, 17, __pyx_L1_error)\n      __pyx_t_1 = (__pyx_temp != 0);\n    }\n\n\n    if (!__pyx_t_1) break;\n```\n\nSubscripted dictionary:\n```c\n/* \"b.pyx\":17\n *·\n * cdef myfunc(d: dict[int]):\n *     while d:             # <<<<<<<<<<<<<<\n *         print('a')\n*/\n  while (1) {\n    __pyx_t_1 = __Pyx_PyObject_IsTrue(__pyx_v_d); if (unlikely((__pyx_t_1 < 0))) __PYX_ERR(0, 17, __pyx_L1_error)\n\n    if (!__pyx_t_1) break;\n```",
